survey_response.review_text: ** ***** ****** ** *** **** ************* I can say this with some authority as we have lived in multiple cities in multiple countries and hence had to have a pediatrician in each place for our kids. Dr Sagar Sharma is the kindest, most patient of them all. He is also highly knowledgeable. He truly cares for the children. My baby has separation anxiety but he still easily goes to Dr Sagar. I think it's because doctor is always calm and cheerful. He answers all our questions and understands our worries. He never brushes off new parents concerns and patiently explains everything. I highly recommend Dr Sagar Sharma to all parents of little ones.

Doctor was nice and handled baby very well. But the Srujana hospital Receptionist was too arrogant and was answering very rudely. I heard the same opinion from other people waiting there as well.  Also, when the transaction got cancelled while making payment she acted as though I have ran away from hospital without making payment. But the fault was with the connection they had in the swiping machine. I suggest to have a good receptionist so that doctor as well as Srujana hospital will not loose its customers/patients.

Experience with doctor was very good. However, the experience with billing counter/receptionist was really bad due to her un welcomingbehaviour. Firstly, she insisted on token to queue management - good. But she started putting people ahead of us without token. When I objected , she tried to cover up with manufactured story. Probably my last visit here :(

After our first consultation with Prashanth P which we were not at all satisfied, we decided to change the doctor and go to doctor Sagar Sharma at Motherhood hospital. 
He was very attentive when we were taking to the doctor as this is our first baby and we had a lot of questions to ask. He answered all of our questions very patiently and made us feel a lot better about the care we are giving our baby. 
Would recommend him definitely.

I am showing both of my daughters to Dr. Sagar sharma. He explains the problem very patiently. Don't hurry in giving medicines. Gives assurance that the health of the kid shall be OK. Spares sufficient amount of time. Suggests natural remedies instead of medicines. Highly recommend.

True to all the reviews I read before going, the doctor is very courteous and patient. Has the rare ability to put parents at ease while explaining what needs to be done. Prescribes only the very essential medication. 
We are Very happy with the interaction.

I took my 4 yr old kid to see the doctor for severe cough and fever. The doctor prescribed a cough syrup, but failed to mention that it’s for paediatric use. ** *** ** ***** *** ********** ** *** ******** ****** *** *** ***** **** ***** **** ***** ******* ** *** ************ ** * * ** **** **** ** *** ***** ** *** ******* *** ********** Will never be going back to Srujana hospital or to Dr Sagar Sharma. Horrible experience!!

Dr Sagar is such a nice person, the politeness, the smiling a face and the way he handles the kids are his unique qualities. As parents we feel that once we consult Sagar the kids should be fine and it's true. He prescribes what is good for the kids and never given anything that would temporarily arrests the situation and leads to side effects. ** ** *** ** **** ************** ** **** *****

Well experienced doctor, always suggests less medicine. Explains issues and remedies very patiently.  Handles babies happily with a friendly nature. We have visited him many times for my baby for both illness and vaccination . each and Everytime we have felt satisfied for consulting him.

Dr. Sagar is a very experienced doctor, and he put my baby at ease immediately. He was gentle with my baby during the check up. Dr. Sagar explained the issue and the steps to resolve it very patiently and also answered all my queries.
I would definitely recommend Dr. Sagar for new parents in and around electronic city.

Thank you Doctor.

Amit & Doris
